kpi_info.title: DC_HSUPA_UE_SUM (M5005C36)
kpi_info.use: The sum of all allocated DC-HSUPA users during the measurement period. The combined amount of DC-HSUPA users of the primary + secondary cell is updated to the primary cell. UPDATED: The number of allocated DC-HSUPA users is sampled with 40 ms periods and all the samples are summed to the counter. The counter is updated only in the primary cell.

kpi_info.title: MAX_DC_HSUPA_USERS (M5005C37)
kpi_info.use: The maximum number of allocated DC-HSUPA users during the measurement period. The combined amount of DC users of the primary + secondary cell is updated to the primary cell.UPDATED: The number of allocated DC-HSUPA users is sampled with 40 ms period and the maximum value of all samples during the measurement period are updated to the counter. The counter is updated only in the primary cell.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DCHSUPA_USERS_2C_SUM (M5005C38)
kpi_info.use: The number of active DC-HSUPA users, which use both carriers for transmission during the measurement period. UPDATED:The number of active DC-HSUPA users using both carriers (primary and secondary) sampled within 40 ms period and all the samples are summed to the counters. The counter is updated only in the primary cell.

kpi_info.title: ACTIVE_DCHSUPA_USERS_1C_SUM (M5005C39)
kpi_info.use: The number of active DC-HSUPA users, which use only one carrier (primary or secondary) for transmission during the measurement period. UPDATED: The number of active DC-HSUPA users using only one carrier (primary or secondary) are sampled with 40 ms period and all the samples are summed to the counters. The counter is updated only in the primary cell.

kpi_info.title: PIC_ACTIVE (M5005C40)
kpi_info.use: The number of samples for monitoring relative time of PIC active state. UPDATED:The counter is incremented by one on each 100ms if cell PIC state is active.

kpi_info.title: PIC_INACTIVE (M5005C41)
kpi_info.use: The number of samples for monitoring relative time of PIC inactive state. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one on each 100ms if cell PIC state is inactive.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_PROMO_DL_AAR (M5005C42)
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI promotions in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is higher than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as promotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in promotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEMOT_DL_AAR (M5005C43)
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI demotions in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is lower than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as demotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter incremented by one when SPI change results in demotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEF_DL_AAR (M5005C44)
kpi_info.use: Number of times the SPI is returned to its default value in the downlink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is equal to the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered by this counter. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE and multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell. UPDATED: The counter is incremented when SPI change results in SPI returning to its default value.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_PROMO_UL_AAR (M5005C45)
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI promotions in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is higher than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as promotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in promotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEMOT_UL_AAR (M5005C46)
kpi_info.use: Number of SPI demotions in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is lower than the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered as demotion. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented by one when SPI change results in demotion of SPI.

kpi_info.title: N_SPI_DEF_UL_AAR (M5005C47)
kpi_info.use: Number of times the SPI is returned to its default value in the uplink direction. Any SPI change where new SPI is equal to the default SPI received from the RNC in the NBAP RL Setup/Reconfiguration message is considered by this counter. The counter considers all cases of single PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE in the cell and not the cases of multiple PS NRT MAC-d queues per UE. UPDATED: The counter is incremented when SPI change results in SPI returning to its default value.

kpi_info.title: DENOM_DC_HSUPA_USERS (M5005C48)
kpi_info.use: The number of samples of M5005C36 (SUM OF DC HSUPA USERS) needed for monitoring the average number of allocated DC-HSUPA users. UPDATED: The counter is updated by value 1 when the number of users is sampled periodically.

kpi_info.title: SUM_DC_HSUPA_DATA_2C (M5005C49)
kpi_info.use: The sum of data volume of active DC-HSUPA user scheduled in two carriers (the primary and/or the secondary). UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE, when the primary is active or the secondary is active or both carriers are active at the sampling moment. The counter is updated in the primary cell only.

kpi_info.title: SUM_DC_HSUPA_DATA_PRI_C (M5005C50)
kpi_info.use: The sum of data volume of active DC-HSUPA users scheduled in the primary carrier. UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE, when primary carrier is active at the sampling moment. The counter is updated to the primary carrier only.

kpi_info.title: SUM_DC_HSUPA_DATA_SEC_C (M5005C51)
kpi_info.use: The sum of data volume of active DC-HSUPA users scheduled in the secondary carrier. UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE, when the secondary carrier is active at the sampling moment. The counter is updated to the secondary carrier only.

kpi_info.title: SUM_PDU_DC_HSUPA_USERS_2C (M5005C52)
kpi_info.use: The number of 2 ms TTI MAC-i PDUs (received by BTS) sent by DC-HSUPA users on the primary and/or the secondary carrier. UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE and both carriers are used or the primary carrier is used or the secondary carrier is used for data transmission at the sampling moment. The counter is incremented only when real UL transmission occurs. The counter is updated in the primary cell only.

kpi_info.title: SUM_PDU_DC_HSUPA_USERS_PRI_C (M5005C53)
kpi_info.use: The number of 2 ms TTI MAC-i PDUs (received by BTS) sent by DC-HSUPA users on the primary carrier. UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE and the primary carrier is used for data transmission at the sampling moment. The counter is incremented only when real UL transmission occurs. The counter is updated in the primary cell only.

kpi_info.title: SUM_PDU_DC_HSUPA_USERS_SEC_C (M5005C54)
kpi_info.use: The number of 2 ms TTI MAC-i PDUs (received by BTS) sent by DC-HSUPA users on the secondary carrier. UPDATED: The counter is updated when BTS receives a MAC-i PDU with 2 ms TTI from UE and the secondary carrier is used for data transmission at the sampling moment. The counter is incremented only when real UL transmission occurs. The counter is updated in the secondary cell only.
